For which of the following primary counts will A win?
ENGLISH.EASSY_DETAILS:
DIRECTIONS for questions 9 to 12: Answer these questions on the basis of the information given below.

Three persons - A, B and C - play a series of games with coins. In each game, they place some coins on a table and pick the coins in turns, starting with A, then B, then C and then A and so on. Each person, in his turn, has to pick either one or two coins. In any game, the number of coins with which the game starts is termed as the primary count of that game. In each game, they get points according to the following conditions:

  1. The person who picks the last coin is the winner of that game and hence gets two points.

  2. The person whose turn is next to the winner of that game gets one point.

  3. The person whose turn is before the winner of that game gets no points.

Also each person plays intelligently and tries to get the maximum possible points.
